<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hey all!</p> <p>I have this custom backend I&#39;m working on:</p> <pre><code>(defun company-sample-backend (command &amp;optional arg &amp;rest ignored) (interactive (list &#39;interactive)) (let ((people (org-ql-select (concat org-dir &quot;/contacts.org&quot;) &#39;(level 1) :action #&#39;org-get-heading))) (cl-case command (interactive (company-begin-backend &#39;company-sample-backend)) (prefix (and (eq major-mode &#39;org-mode) (company-grab-symbol))) (candidates (my/contacts-candidates arg)) (post-completion (company-thing arg))))) </code></pre> <p>It works well, so far. However, what I&#39;d like is to have this backend &quot;kick in&quot; <em>only</em> when I press <code>@</code>. I&#39;m not entirely sure how to achieve this. I assume it needs to be done in the <code>prefix</code> logic, but my attempts don&#39;t seem to work. I&#39;m hoping someone has done this and can show me the (probably simple) solution.</p> <p>Thanks!</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/codethrasher"> /u/codethrasher </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wd0quw/custom_companybackends_only_trigger_backend_on/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wd0quw/custom_companybackends_only_trigger_backend_on/">[comments]</a></span>